  "$comment": "Single source of truth for supported ATAK versions AND compatibility bands. Read by the justfile (list-versions, sync-sdk, build) and by app/build.gradle, which DERIVES the atakVersion flavors, BuildConfig.TARGET_ATAK_VERSION, manifest plugin-api stamps, and the band source-set wiring from it. Add a version = one row here + its main.jar in sdk/ — band membership is derived (a new version lands on the correct side of every existing bandPair automatically); add a bandPair only for a genuinely NEW API break. 'pluginApi' is the version half of the manifest plugin-api (com.atakmap.app@<pluginApi>.<FLAVOR>); pluginApiVerified=true means the value was confirmed against the merged manifest of a real build. 'ideDefault' marks the flavor Android Studio selects.",
  "$bandComment": "Each bandPair is one real API break: versions BELOW firstPlusVersion compile src/<pre>/java, versions AT/ABOVE compile src/<plus>/java (identical FQNs per pair; exactly one side per APK). Byte-level evidence: docs/analysis/byte-confirmation.md.",
